                "href": "/profile/Rebecca-Metz"
            },
            "answer_text": "As others have said, it depends. Multi-camera comedies, better known as sit coms, typically shoot an episode per 4- or 5-day week. It's a pretty luxurious schedule. Single camera comedies take a bit longer, and hour-long dramas longer than that - commonly around 8 days per episode. And the hours on single camera shows are generally much longer than on multi cam. To save money, more and more shows are doing something called \u2018cross boarding,\u2019 which involves shooting multiple episodes at once. So they'll set up at one location and shoot everything that happens there across several episodes. On shoots like that, there's no standard number of days per episode. ",
