                "name": "Dustin Rosemark",
                "href": "/profile/Dustin-Rosemark"
            },
            "answer_text": "Standard model for a \u2018old hollywood\u2019 show is 1 week. That is 6 days on and 1 day off. Next week is 6 days on 1 day off. Classic shows like Star Trek the Next Generation, CSI, Law and Order were all shot in this manner. Television is rapidly changing however as HBO, Showtime, Netflix and Amazon are redefining how we view (and watch) conventional television. Instead of treating the show as a week-to-week sort of endeavor they are often running the show as a top-down endeavor. The show Stranger Things is shot in this manner, with production set up as one 8-hour long movie instead of an episodic breakdown. ",
